bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Martha Baird Rockefeller Fund for Music was founded in 1957, as a private philanthropy, by Martha Baird Rockefeller with monies received from the estate of John D. Rockefeller Jr. Incorporated in 1962, the Fund's interest centered on young solo artists, who received support directly through individual grants or indirectly through contributions to performance organizations that offered advanced training and employment. Funds were also allocated to: aid symphony orchestras, opera companies, and other performing groups and organizations, including but not limited to the presenting of concerts to benefit local communities; to enable schools of music and other educational institutions to carry out programs and projects contributing to the training of students; to support festivals and other activities devoted to the advancement of musical knowledge and culture; and to establish or aid research in the field of musicology.

Until Mrs. Rockefeller's death in 1971, the Fund was supported by her contributions of $600,000 annually. Her will provided for an unrestricted bequest to the fund of $5,000,000, and the trustees elected to continue the program at the same level until funds were exhausted. The Fund was dissolved in 1982.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: This collection was donated to RAC in 1983. Record transfers began in the early 1980s and continued through 2005.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Rockefeller Archive Center has legal title, copyright and literary property rights to this collection, in so far as it holds them.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

In accordance with stipulations of the collecton agreemen - the project files on grants and declinations were unavailable for research until 1988. Administration files were unavailable for research until 2003.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Project files for individual and institutional grant recipients and declinations. Records often include applications, funding requests, grant actions, correspondence, and further background or supportive documentation.
Further content will be added to this finding aid as additional archival records are processed and made available for research (Spring 2018).
